Short Description
Coming in many different colors and sizes, Thingamakin Juveniles are wild animalistic dust pests that can be found anywhere on The Continent.
Although they're uncommon, it's mostly likely due to the fact they're often scared of humanoids. When frightened, they retreat into their object shells and scutter away.

Their dusty bodies let them burrow their way into objects they deem as "suitable shells". However, doing so also damages the object after the Thingamakin eventually moves on and abandons it.
However, it's been noted that they don't damage intentionally, as they prefer items with internals already-present as their shells. Things like devices, the wedges of doors, or even storage units. When abandoning these types of objects, they leave no trace of damage behind.

