Abilities
Full-Body Senses 👁️👃👂
Thingamakin perceive all 5 senses through their dusty bodies. They taste, feel, hear, smell, and see through their archose-like dust, similar to ⁠Archkin.
However, since it's only their dusty forms that share this trait, when retreating into their object shell, all their senses dull out.

Experience Consumption
Rather than needing food, water, or even air to live— Thingamakin persist through Experiences and gaining/perpetuation new Memories, a trait shared with Archubi.
However, unlike their distant ⁠Alterants cousins, Thingamakin cannot absorb memories from others. Rather, they must gain memories naturally.

If a Thingamakin cowers away for too long and stagnates, it can quickly lead to finality.

Overview
Thingamakin are odd critters as there are still many mysteries surrounding them. Notably, nobody knows how they reproduce. More of them just... pop up. When asking the sentient ⁠Thingamakin Elders about this, they don't seem to have an answer either.

Speaking of their Elder counterparts, that's another bizarre case with these little things.
Thingamakin slowly gain sentience as they get bigger and older. They start out animalistic, but after their 10 years of expected lifespan, if one simply... keeps surviving... it eventually develops ⁠Humans-level sentience.
This makes it a moral dilemma whether or not it's fine to kill Thingamakin, let alone consume them. It doesn't help that their bodies taste exactly like human.

They're technically considered ⁠Alterants (Modified Humans) as they were once ⁠Humans. But the result of their creation produced the furthest and closest attempt at creating new ⁠Archkin.
Essentially, they're "Failed ⁠Archkin".